{
  "title": "test_genie",
  "description": "This space enables exploration and analysis of daily historical weather data for the top 50 global cities, supporting business insights and operational planning.\n\n**Capabilities:**\n- Compare weather patterns (temperature, precipitation, humidity, etc.) across major cities and time periods.\n- Analyze correlations between weather factors and business outcomes, such as supply chain risks, energy demand forecasts, and sales projections.\n- Identify trends, regional variability, and outliers in weather conditions to inform risk management and targeted marketing strategies.\n- Build visualizations (e.g., time series, heatmaps) to better understand weather impact on economic activities.\n- Access both imperial and metric unit datasets for flexible analysis needs.\n- View additional data offerings via the [Databricks Marketplace listing.](https://marketplace.databricks.com/consumer/listings/235b45d2-d625-4c1c-90a2-68e4568dda40)\n\n**Limitations:**\n- Data covers only a one-month sample and a limited set of cities and weather attributes.\n- Not suited for production use or detailed long-term trend analysis.\n- Lacks certain advanced weather parameters and extended historical range available in the full AccuWeather Data Suite.",
